    en: "Mental Hygiene Law Section 33.16 creates a distinct access framework for mental health, substance use, and developmental disability records that is separate from HIPAA and from general medical-records access under PHL 18. A 'qualified person' — usually the patient or a legal representative — may request access to their clinical record from a NYS-licensed or operated mental health facility. The provider may deny access in part if a clinician determines the information would reasonably be expected to cause substantial harm to the patient or another person. A denied patient may appeal to the Clinical Record Access Review Committee and, from there, to state court. The statute specifically voids any waiver by a patient of the right to inspect or correct their record."
